<HEADLINE> FBI's Most Wanted List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 10 people on the FBI's Most Wanted list, why they're wanted  
and when they were added: 
</P>
<P>
	--Donald Eugene Webb, murder of Pennsylvania police chief, 1981.  
</P>
<P>
	--Victor Manuel Gerena, $7 million robbery of securities company  
in Connecticut, 1984. 
</P>
<P>
	--Arthur Lee Washington, associated with the Black Liberation  
Army, twice convicted of armed robbery, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	--Agustin Vasquez-Mendoza, killing of a Drug Enforcement  
Administration agent, 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	--Glen Stewart Godwin, escaped murderer and cocaine dealer, 1996.  
</P>
<P>
	--Ramon Eduardo Arellano-Felix, drug conspiracy and smuggling,  
1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Harry Joseph Bowman, motorcycle gang figure, wanted for  
drug-related racketeering, including murder, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Eric Robert Rudolph, three Atlanta-area bombings, including the  
1996 Olympic park bombing in Atlanta, in which a woman died, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--James Charles Kopp, 1999.  
</P>
<P>
	--Osama Bin Laden, 1999.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
