<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Supermarket Suspect Accused of Rape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- A man accused of gunning down four people in a  
supermarket also raped an escort service employee an hour before 
the rampage and told her he planned to kill the first 19 people he 
saw, prosecutors said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Zane Floyd, 23, was to be arraigned Monday on four counts of  
murder and one count of attempted murder, but prosecutor Bill Koot 
asked for a delay until Wednesday to allow for time to add sexual 
assault charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Twenty-five people were in an Albertsons supermarket on Thursday  
when Floyd allegedly entered with a pump-action shotgun. 
Investigators said he gunned down some victims as he came upon 
them, and chased others down. Four employees were killed and one 
seriously wounded. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities were still trying to determine the motive.  
</P>
<P>
	Koot said the 20-year-old escort service employee was told by  
her assailant that he had 19 rounds of ammunition and planned to 
kill the first 19 people he saw. 
</P>
<P>
	``For some unexplained reason, he let her go rather than killing  
her,'' Koot said. ``He threatened to kill her, and he was going to 
kill her, but then he let her go.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In court Monday, Floyd showed no emotion. He was ordered held  
without bond, and a public defender was appointed for him. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990607.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-07 11:30:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against most other major  
currencies in European trading Monday -- and the battered euro fell 
to a new record low before staging a modest recovery. Gold prices 
rose. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0293, down from $1.0318 Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	But the currency of 11 European Union countries was up from  
$1.0260 that it hit soon after trading started with more bad news 
for the euro -- the breakdown of talks on a Serb withdrawal from 
Kosovo. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Friday: 120.91 Japanese  
yen, down from 121.84; 1.5403 Swiss francs, down from 1.5409; 
1.4712 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4715. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6048, down from $1.6063.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar was worth 121.22 yen,  
while the euro was worth $1.0282 and the British pound was worth 
$1.6002. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 1.9002 German marks, up from 1.8996; 
6.3728 French francs, up from 6.3710; 2.1410 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.1404; and 1,881.15 Italian lire, up from 1,880.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $265.20 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$264.50 on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $265.25, up from $264.45.  
</P>
<P>
	Earlier gold rose 80 cents in Hong Kong to close at $266.25.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $4.96 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$4.88. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
