<HEADLINE> Two Students Die From Electrocution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MAUMEE, Ohio (AP) -- Two college students working summer jobs  
died Monday when a football goal post they were moving touched a 
high-voltage electrical wire at a high school. 
</P>
<P>
	Police found Dominic Hess and Wesley Shook, both 19, on the  
ground, with the post leaning against a 7,200-volt wire that was 
about 30 feet high. A third worker was dazed and suffered minor 
burns and cuts. 
</P>
<P>
	In another electrocution, a man and his teen-age son were  
electrocuted Sunday in their backyard pool in Griffith, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
	Gregory Taylor was cleaning the pool with a power washer and  
investigators are not sure whether the appliance fell in while 
Taylor was in the water or whether it fell first and Taylor went in 
afterward. 
</P>
<P>
	Taylor's 17-year-old son, Nick, apparently found his father in  
the pool and went in to help. He was also electrocuted. 
  	   	
</P>
