<HEADLINE> Tigers Option Anderson to Toledo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Pitcher Matt Anderson, who jumped from Double-A  
to the majors with the Detroit Tigers last year, will get a taste 
of Triple-A after all. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson, whose fastball has been clocked at 103 mph, was  
optioned to the club's International League team at Toledo after 
Monday night's 9-4 interleague win over Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
	Nelson Cruz, who was recalled to fill Anderson's spot on the  
roster, will start Tuesday night in place of Justin Thompson, who 
complained of back spasms Monday. Thompson's condition was listed 
as day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson, the No. 1 overall pick by the Tigers in the 1997  
draft, was sensational in his rookie season, going 5-1 with a 3.27 
ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	This season, he was 1-0 with a 2.18 ERA in his first 19  
appearances, striking out 22 batters on 20 2-3 innings. However, he 
allowed 11 runs in three innings over his final five outings before 
being optioned. 
</P>
<P>
	Cruz, making his second appearance on the Tigers' roster this  
season, has won seven of eight decisions at Toledo, compiling a 
2.73 ERA in 62 2-3 innings. Two of his four complete games for the 
Mud Hens were shutouts. 
</P>
<P>
	He pitched in three games out of the bullpen for Detroit between  
May 4-11, then was returned to Toledo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
