<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AlliedSignal To Buy Honeywell  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- AlliedSignal is buying Honeywell for $14.82  
billion in stock, strengthening its aerospace business with the 
addition of Honeywell's control systems. The new company will take 
the Honeywell name and the AlliedSignal headquarters in Morristown, 
N.J. Honeywell's headquarters in Minneapolis will be closed. The 
two companies will cut a total of 4,500 jobs, or 3.6 percent, of 
their combined work force. AlliedSignal makes equipment ranging 
from aircraft engines and collision early-warning systems, to 
wheels and brakes. Honeywell makes control systems for aircraft, 
homes and commercial buildings, such as automatic thermostats for 
heating. AlliedSignal stock rose 4 7/16 to 62 13/16 and Honeywell 
gained 7 to 112. 

</P>
<P>
	IBM-Microsoft Relations Outlined  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- An IBM manager accused Microsoft today of  
offering discounts worth tens of millions of dollars to IBM to 
sacrifice its rival computer operating system and to stop 
distributing software from key competitors. Garry Norris, a 
mid-level IBM executive, said Microsoft Chairman Bill Gates was so 
angry about IBM's defiance that he overheard the billionaire 
screaming during a private phone call in July 1995 to another IBM 
executive in the room. Norris testified that IBM saw the total fees 
it pays to Microsoft rise from $40 million in 1996 to $440 million 
last year because it rejected Microsoft's alleged overtures not to 
compete. Microsoft shares closed at 80 1/4, up 11/16. IBM stock gained 
4 1/2 to 120 1/2. 

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Higher; Dow Up 109.54  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose for a third straight session today  
as corporate mergers and bargain prices lured investors back to a 
market that is again inching toward record heights. The Dow Jones 
industrial average closed up 109.54 at 10,909.38. The Nasdaq 
composite rose 49.71 to 2,528.05. Trading got a boost today from 
the announcement of several mergers, particularly a $14.82 billion 
deal between AlliedSignal and Honeywell that creates an aerospace 
parts-and-electronics conglomerate. IBM's stock price rose past 120 
today after a J.P. Morgan analyst said IBM could reach 150 within 
the year, citing strong sales of its electronic business software. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10909.38 + 109.54
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1724  Declines 1239  Unchgd  577
