<HEADLINE> Microsoft Ships Office 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	REDMOND, Wash. (AP) -- The new millennium is already here for  
many computers systems as Microsoft Corp. began shipping its 
Microsoft Office 2000 today. 
</P>
<P>
	The new technology, which is fully compatible with Office 97, is  
being unveiled to the public this afternoon at The Metreon Sony 
Entertainment Center in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	Office 2000 further blurs the line between PC operations and the  
World Wide Web. 
</P>
<P>
	Microsoft added HTML, the Web's basic document structure, as a  
companion file format, which will allow for easy conversion from a 
PC document to an Internet-ready document without losing data or 
formatting. 
</P>
<P>
	Documents can also make a ``round trip'' into HTML and back  
again to the PC format, according statement issued by the 
Redmond-based company. 
</P>
<P>
	The Premium version of Office 2000 also includes a Web site  
creation and management program. 
</P>
<P>
	Office 2000 also targets small companies with its Small Business  
Tools package, offering programs for customer management, financial 
management, business planning and direct mail. 
</P>
<P>
	The basic 2000 version also includes upgrades to Office word  
processing, spreadsheet and e-mail features. 
</P>
<P>
	Prices for upgrades range from $249 to $499, the company said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
