<HEADLINE> Oregonian Arrested for Blowing Dart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A man wearing a black Ninja warrior costume and  
swinging a sword in Central Park hit a passer-by in the head with a 
blow dart, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The victim, struck by a 3-inch dart which fell off his head, was  
treated at a hospital Sunday night and released. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael Tucker, 29, of Salem, Ore., was arrested and charged  
with assault and criminal possession of a weapon. 
</P>
<P>
	Tucker was found in the Ramble, a woodsy area of Central Park,  
with a 26-inch sword, a dartgun, and two 6-inch knives and a 7-inch 
knife strapped to his legs. He also had grappling hooks and a set 
of climbing claws, court papers said. 
