<HEADLINE> Microsoft Launches Office 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Microsoft formally launched Office 2000  
today, integrating Web site design tools into the first major 
upgrade of its word-processing and spreadsheet package in more than 
two years. 
</P>
<P>
	Office 2000 comes in five different versions and should be  
available in stores on June 10. 
</P>
<P>
	The upgrade to the most popular Office 97 version, Office 2000  
Professional includes the FrontPage Web site authoring tool and 
PhotoDraw 2000 business graphics software. The suggested retail 
price is $309 for upgrades, $599 for new users. 
</P>
<P>
	``Its biggest benefits are for companies that are going to be  
doing a lot of Web authoring,'' said Rob Enderle, an analyst with 
Giga Information Group. ``You can create and maintain a much more 
professional Web site.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But Office 2000 has arrived too late for many companies using  
Microsoft's software in the workplace, many of which may delay 
upgrading until next year due to fears about the Year 2000 bug, 
Enderle said. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 100 million customers worldwide use Office 97. The  
software suite accounted for about one-third of Microsoft's $14.5 
billion in revenues for the fiscal year 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Office 97 accounts for about 90 percent of the market for  
business productivity software. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
