<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Higher / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks edged higher Tuesday morning in  
light trading prior to the release of a key economic indicator 
later this week. The dollar rose against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average added 16.10 points,  
or 0.09 percent, to 16,491.99 at the end of the morning session. On 
Monday, the average gained 175.14 points, or 1.07 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 121.23 yen, up 0.39 yen from late Monday in  
Tokyo and also above its late New York level of 120.80 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, strength on Wall Street pushed up Tokyo  
share prices, but many investors were holding back to await the 
release Thursday of gross domestic product figures for the January 
to March quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors also were awaiting news about government plans to  
compile a supplementary budget to stimulate the economy, traders 
said. Also sending investors to the sidelines was the outcome of a 
government report on industrial competitiveness, expected to be 
released next week. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 109.54  
points, or 1 percent, to 10,909.38. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 2.92 points, or 0.22 percent, to 1,331.57. The 
TOPIX closed up 12.12 points, or 0.92 percent Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, yen-bearish comments by Japan's  
influential vice finance minister for international affairs, Eisuke 
Sakakibara, boosted the dollar against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	``As a general rule, it's undesirable for the yen to strengthen  
too much before the economy recovers,'' Sakakibara told reporters 
Tuesday morning. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was quoted at 124.68 yen, up from  
124.47 yen late Monday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond fell to 1.5800  
percent from Monday's finish of 1.6650 percent, driving its price 
up to 98.44 yen from 97.72 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
