<HEADLINE> Boles Returns As Marlins Manager </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- The pitch appeared to be six inches outside.  
Florida Marlins manager John Boles, recovering at home from neck 
and back ailments, watched on TV as one of his players was called 
out on strikes with the bases loaded. 
</P>
<P>
	``I knew I was healthy then, when I lifted up the TV and threw  
it out the window,'' Boles joked. 
</P>
<P>
	After missing 13 games in two stints, Boles returned to work  
Monday -- just in time for a rainout. The Marlins' game against the 
Baltimore Orioles was rescheduled as part of a doubleheader 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Boles was sidelined for two days following emergency back  
surgery, came back to work -- perhaps too soon -- and sprained his 
neck, which sent him home for another 11 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Other than a little stiffness, Boles said he feels fine now, and  
he returns to a team playing its best baseball of the season. The 
Marlins have scored 44 runs during a five-game winning streak that 
included a three-game weekend sweep at Tampa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was the best medicine a person could get, watching the team  
scoring 10 runs a game in Tampa,'' Boles said. ``It was fun to 
watch. I feel like a new person.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fredi Gonzalez went 6-7 as interim manager.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
