<HEADLINE> Man Charged in Hit-and-Run Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- A 19-year-old man drunkenly killed a woman with  
his car and laughed as he drove off, prosecutors say. 
</P>
<P>
	James Abramofsky Jr. pleaded innocent to vehicular homicide,  
operating under the influence of alcohol and leaving the scene of a 
deadly accident. He was ordered held on $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
	Abramofsky allegedly drove his car into 56-year-old Leona  
Doucette on Saturday as she walked across the street. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Doucette landed on the hood and slid off when the car  
stopped, said Jim Borghesani, a spokesman for prosecutors. 
Abramofsky then ran over her, and witnesses said he was laughing as 
he drove away, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	Abramofsky's lawyer, William Korman, said ``it's true that a  
terrible tragedy did occur,'' but he denied Abramofsky laughed. 
  	   	
