<HEADLINE> Jones Long Jumping at Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Marion Jones, ranked No. 1 in the world in  
the long jump, will compete in that event Saturday at the Pontiac 
Grand Prix Invitational in Raleigh, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
	USA Track &AMP; Field announced Monday the entry of Jones, who also  
was No. 1 in the world last year in the 100 and 200 meters. 
</P>
<P>
	The meet, to be held within the framework of the final day of  
the Foot Locker Championships for high school athletes, will be 
comprised of nine events. The men will compete in the 100, 200, 
400, 110 hurdles and 400 hurdles. The women will contest the 400, 
800, pole vault and long jump. 
</P>
