<HEADLINE> Pet Tiger Mauls 10-Year-Old Girl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YORKTOWN, Texas (AP) -- A 10-year-old girl died after being  
mauled by one of her stepfather's pet tigers. 
</P>
<P>
	Lorin Casey Villafana died of head and neck injuries. She was in  
a cage Sunday night with her stepfather, who is licensed to have 
the two tigers and takes them to exotic animal shows across Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	``Her father was brushing the female tiger and all of a sudden  
the male tiger jumped on the little girl and dragged her through 
the cage,'' Police Chief Guy Nobles said Monday. ``The stepfather 
finally got the tiger to let her go, and he picked her up and got 
her out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The stepfather was not injured. Authorities would not say  
whether they were considering charges against him. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
