<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pregnant Sr. Gets Degree Privately </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ELIZABETHTOWN, Ky. (AP) -- A senior at a Christian high school  
who was stripped of her valedictorian title and barred from 
graduation because she is pregnant received her diploma in a 
private ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
	Leah Carr, 18, who had straight A's at Dove Christian Academy,  
got her diploma on Sunday, two days after her classmates graduated. 
Nearly 100 people were on hand to support her. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Carr had admitted to school officials that she was pregnant  
and asked forgiveness. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have no regrets about confessing to the board or about  
keeping my baby,'' she said. ``I know it's not going to be easy, 
but I believe my faith in God and the support from my family and 
friends will help me through.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The school is operated by the First Assembly of God in Radcliff.  
The pastor and the principal have refused to comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Carr said she plans to attend community college and hopes to  
become a nurse practitioner. 
</P>
<P>
	Her mother said she was proud of her daughter.  
</P>
<P>
	``I often tell my children that you are not a failure unless you  
don't get up when you fall,'' Lisa Carr said. ``Like any parent, 
I'm proud that my daughter has maintained a mature, Christian 
attitude through all of this.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
