<HEADLINE>  Stocks Push Ahead; Dow Up 92.45 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose broadly today as corporate mergers  
helped distract investors from lingering concerns about inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	At 3 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 92.45 at 10,892.29. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's  
500 index was up 5.73 at 1,333.48, and the Nasdaq composite index 
was up 45.23 at 2,523.57. 
</P>
<P>
	Volume was light as traders already began looking ahead to  
Friday, when the government's producer price index is expected to 
