<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  McGwire Misses Kansas City Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Mark McGwire did not start the opener of  
the St. Louis Cardinals' three-game series at Kansas City tonight 
because of a sore back. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire took part in pregame drills, including batting practice.  
But Shawon Dunston started at first base. McGwire said he probably 
will play Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``My back is a little sore, I did that for the fans,'' McGwire  
said after hitting several home runs during batting practice, 
including a long one into the shrubbery under the video board in 
left-center. ``My back has been killing me for two-plus weeks 
now.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The stadium was sold out for the first time since opening day as  
many Cardinals fans made the trip from St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, a game with the Cincinnati Reds was postponed when an  
electrical explosion caused a power loss to a bank of lights. The 
Royals were swept in a doubleheader Saturday and fans endured a 
63-minute rain delay Sunday as the Reds won 14-3. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire is hitting .266 with 17 homers and 42 RBIs.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
