<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 40-Something Fights Dominate Card </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Someone said it looked like five guys getting  
ready to make retirement speeches. 
</P>
<P>
	Larry Holmes, James ``Bonecrusher'' Smith, Tim Witherspoon, Greg  
Page and Juan LaPorte, ranging in age from 49 down to 39, however, 
were in New York today to talk about fighting on a pay-per-view 
card June 19 in the Crown Coliseum at Fayetteville, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
	The show kicks off what is planned as a Legends of Boxing  
series, and promoter Cozell McQueen was said the age limits are 35 
to 50. 
</P>
<P>
	``So you'll let a 50-year-old man fight,'' McQueen was asked.  
</P>
<P>
	``If he's still living,'' shouted Holmes, who will turn 50 Nov.  
3. 
</P>
<P>
	Holmes beat Smith and Witherspoon defeated Page in 1984 in  
heavyweight title fights. Retirements, not difficult negotiations, 
held up the rematches for which there has been no particular public 
clamor. 
</P>
<P>
	McQueen said as of Monday 1,200 tickets ranging from $20 to $150  
had been sold. The arena holds 11,500. The pay-per-view price is 
$19.95. 
</P>
<P>
	LaPorte, a 39-year-old former featherweight contender, will  
fight a 10-round junior middleweight bout against 43-year-old Billy 
Costello, WBC super lightweight champion in 1984-85. Costello did 
not attend the news conference. 
</P>
<P>
	The idea for Legends of Boxing was that of Smith, a 46-year-old  
native of North Carolina who came out of retirement to fight three 
times last year. On July 4, he was stopped after one round against 
Joe Bugner when he dislocated his right shoulder while throwing a 
punch. 
</P>
<P>
	The Smith-Holmes fight will be a 12-round bout for the Legends  
heavyweight championship. Holmes stopped Smith on a cut in the 12th 
round in defense of the IBF title Nov. 9, 1984. Holmes held the WBC 
or IBF titles from 1978 to 1985. Smith won the WBA title by 
stopping Witherspoon in the first round Dec. 12, 1986, and lost it 
on points to Mike Tyson March 17, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
	``Time flies when you're having fun,'' said Holmes, who fought  
relatively often from 1991 through 1997. He did not fight last year 
when he signed to fight George Foreman, but that match was 
canceled. 
</P>
<P>
	``If an individual can still get in shape to perform, then I  
don't see why they should retire him from what he loves doing,'' 
Holmes said. 
</P>
<P>
	``As long as two guys who know how to fight and are in the same  
age category and are in shape, I don't see anything wrong with 
it,'' said Smith, a North Carolina boxing commissioner in 1995-97. 
</P>
<P>
	The Witherspoon-Page bout is scheduled for 10 rounds. The  
41-year-old Witherspoon outpointed the 40-year-old Page for the 
vacant WBC title Dec. 12, 1984. Witherspoon later won the WBA 
title, and Page also became a WBA champion. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith showed up at the news conference with a bottle of  
something he called Power Punch, which he hopes to market. Asked 
what is in it, Smith said: 
</P>
<P>
	``It's fruit and vegetables and a lot of other ingredients that  
make you feel young.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
